Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to boil. Zest, then halve the @lemon{1}. Cut one half into wedges. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}. Thinly slice the @basil{1%ounce} leaves. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @red bell peppers{2}.

Toss the bell peppers on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until slightly caramelized.

Heat @butter{2%tbsp} in a pan over medium heat. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} and toss for ~{2-3%minutes}, until golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Add the @farfalle pasta{12%oz} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1 cup pasta water.

While the pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over high heat. Season the @shrimp{16%oz} with the @Italian seasoning{2%tsp}, salt and pepper. Add the shrimp to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{1-2%minutes}, until almost opaque. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, until fragrant.

Toss the pasta and roasted peppers into the pan with the shrimp. Add the lemon zest, @butter{2%tbsp}, half the basil, 1 cup pasta water, and a squeeze of lemon. Bring to a boil and toss for ~{3-4%minutes}, until a sauce has formed. Taste and season with salt, pepper, and lemon juice, if needed. Serve topped with the crispy breadcrumbs, remaining basil, and a drizzle of olive oil. Enjoy!

> It's hard not to love farfalle—their tiny bowtie shape is just precious. Torested red peppers and a sprinkling of crunchy breadcrumbs give this 30-minute pasta a special touch.